        "content": "<p>In <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/14866\">#14866</a>, we define various <code>scoped instance</code>s, and the linter protests that they should be <code>theorem</code>s and not <code>def</code>sâ€¦ How can we make it happy?</p>",
        "id": 452441570,
        "sender_full_name": "Antoine Chambert-Loir",
        "timestamp": 1721337128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>They have data right?</p>",
        "id": 452442781,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1721337727
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The issue is that <code>instance</code> (even <code>scoped instance</code>) always creates a <code>def</code>. The linter knows to ignore global instances, but doesn't know about scoped instances.</p>",
        "id": 452442880,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1721337793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>E.g., you can use <code>@[scoped instance] theorem</code>.</p>",
        "id": 452442911,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1721337820
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK, thanks!</p>",
